#Text=Depok
#Text=Depok
#Text=is a city in the province of West Java in Indonesia .
#Text=The city , with a population of almost 2 million , is part of the Jabodetabek Greater Jakarta metropolitan area and is just south of the national capital .
#Text=One of the most prestigious universities of the country , the University of Indonesia , is here .
#Text=By car
#Text=There is one main road from Jakarta into Depok , Jalan Margonda Raya , which also passes the University of Indonesia campus .
#Text=It is thus not hard to imagine that the road can be very crowded in the mornings and the evenings .
#Text=Another way in is via the Jagorawi toll road that leads from Jakarta to Bogor .
#Text=Just south of Jakarta , there is an exit to the short Cijago toll road that leads straight to the city centre of Depok .
#Text=This toll road is planned to be extended westwards to South Tangerang .
#Text=By train
#Text=Depok has five railway stations along the railway from Jakarta to Bogor , from north to south being Universitas Indonesia , Pondok Cina , Depok Baru , , and Citayam stations .
#Text=The stations are served by the yellow and red lines of Jakarta 's commuter rail network ( KA Commuter Jabodetabek ) .

#Text=The yellow line runs from Jatinegara station in East Jakarta via a loop through North , West , Central , and South Jakarta to Depok , and then further to either Bogor to the south , or Nambo station to the east .
#Text=Some trains terminate at Depok station and therefore do not call at Citayam .
#Text=The red line runs from Kota station in Jakarta 's old town ( West Jakarta ) via Depok to Bogor .
#Text=Also for this line , some trains terminate at Depok station .
#Text=Ticket prices from Jakarta to Depok are approximately Rp.3,000 .
#Text=Travel time from Jakarta to Depok is between 25 and 70 minutes , depending on the place of departure in Jakarta .
#Text=The railway stations in Depok are not served by long-distance trains .
#Text=Instead , long-distance trains can be taken from Gamvir stations in Jakarta
#Text=By bus
#Text=Next to Depok Baru railway station , there is .
#Text=At the terminal , there is a wide range of minibuses and buses to and from destinations throughout Depok , Jakarta , and the wider conurbation .
#Text=In addition , there are intercity buses to destinations including throughout Western Java , including Bandung and Sukabumi .
#Text=There are no direct buses to and from Jakarta 's Soekarno-Hatta International Airport .
#Text=The nearest bus terminals with direct DAMRI bus airport service are Pasar Minggu in South Jakarta and Kampung Rambutan in East Jakarta .
#Text=Get around
#Text=There are dozens of minibus ( angkot ) routes throughout Depok , with many of them connecting to South Tangerang and Jakarta .
#Text=Angkots follow a fixed route , but there is no fixed schedule and there are no fixed stops .
#Text=To get on , simply raise your hand .
#Text=To get off , simply shout " Kiri !

#Text=, an area south of the modern Depok which is considered to be the foundation of the modern city , was founded by Cornelis Chastelein as a native Christian congregation named  DEPOC " ( De Eerste Protestante Organisatie van Christenen ) .

column1: #Text=This area is inhabited by Christianized former slave families of Cornelis who inherited his land after his death in 1714 , known today as Belanda Depok ( which means " Dutch Depok " , due to their ability to speak Dutch ) .
#Text=The area consists of old colonial-era homes and an old church , which dates back to the year Cornelis died ; its church bell was built in 1675 .
#Text=University of Indonesia campus
#Text=( Universitas Indonesia , UI ) .
#Text=The University of Indonesia has a beautiful campus with several lakes and interesting architecture .
#Text=Do
#Text=Cycling , walking and jogging at the University of Indonesia Campus are common recreational activities during weekends in Depok .
#Text=On Sundays , there is a market just outside of the campus where you can buy cheap things from food to CDs , and from clothes to utensils .
#Text=Buy
#Text=At the end of the year , it 's the durian season ; durian is a tropical fruit sold by locals along the road from Depok to Bogor .
#Text=Durians here are cheap and good enough with price ranging from Rp.5,000-30,000 .
#Text=Do n't hesitate to bargain the price and tell them that you only pay a good one .
#Text=The seller will choose the fruit for you , open a small hole and take a little fruit for you to taste .
#Text=If you 're satisfied with the taste , they will open the whole fruit for you if you want to finish the fruit in their place .
#Text=Depok Town Square
#Text=( Detos ) , Jl .
#Text=Margonda Raya .
#Text=One of the several shopping malls in Depok .
#Text=This mall includes a wide range of shops , cafés , and restaurants , as well as a 21Cineplex cinema .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Along the main roads to Jakarta ( Jalan Margonda Raya ) and Bogor ( Jalan Raya Bogor ) , there are many restaurants with various cuisines , from Sundanese and Javanese to Western .
#Text=Cheap meals can be found especially in student cafés at or around the university campus .
#Text=Drink
#Text=Like other cities in West Java province , Depok has similar drinks .
#Text=The variety of options are young coconut water with ice and palm sugar , mixed chunk fruit and jelly with ice , blended fruit with ice .
#Text=They are refreshing for a really hot day .
#Text=For those who are on diet should drink carefully because they are high energy drinks .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=Hotel Bumi Wiyata
#Text=, Jalan Margonda Raya , ☏ +62217778040 .
#Text=Along Depok 's main road , a three-star hotel with fitness , spa , and swimming pool .
#Text=Double rooms from Rp.750,000 per night .
#Text=Hotel Santika Depok
#Text=, Jalan Margonda Raya Kav . 88 , ☏ +622177219291 .
#Text=Three-star hotel along the main road , between the city centre and the University of Indonesia campus .
#Text=Double rooms from about Rp.500,000 per night .
#Text=The Margo Hotel Depok
#Text=, Jl .
#Text=Margonda Raya No. 358 , ☏ +622129515888 .
#Text=Luxury hotel near the Pondok Cina railway station .
#Text=Double room from about Rp.900,000 per night .
#Text=For longer-term staying , the Margonda Residence Apartments , located on Margonda Raya is quite useful .
#Text=It costs Rp . 1,350,000-1,700,000 per month for a studio room , with a minimal contract of three months .
#Text=As yet , it is the only apartment in Depok although others are being built .

#Text=It is across the road from Universitas Indonesia , on the north part of the city , and thus is safe from much of the traffic jam in the city ( although one still has to negotiate the traffic on the Jakarta side ) .
